.. Junebug command line

Running Junebug
===============

Running junebug is done through the ``jb`` command.

Usage
-----
::

    jb [-h] [--config CONFIG_FILENAME] [--interface INTERFACE]\
    [--port PORT] [--log-file LOGFILE] [--redis-host REDIS_HOST]
    [--redis-port REDIS_PORT] [--redis-db REDIS_DB]
    [--redis-password REDIS_PASS] [--amqp-host AMQP_HOST]
    [--amqp-vhost AMQP_VHOST] [--amqp-port AMQP_PORT]
    [--amqp-user AMQP_USER] [--amqp-password AMQP_PASS]
    [--inbound-message-ttl INBOUND_MESSAGE_TTL]
    [--outbound-message-ttl OUTBOUND_MESSAGE_TTL]


Optional Arguments:
-------------------

-h, --help
    show this help message and exit

--config CONFIG_FILENAME, -c CONFIG_FILENAME
    Path to config file. Optional. Command line options override config options

--interface INTERFACE, -i INTERFACE
    The interface to expose the API on. Defaults to "localhost"

--port PORT, -p PORT
    The port to expose the API on, defaults to "8080"

--log-file LOGFILE, -l LOGFILE
    The file to log to. Defaults to not logging to a file

--redis-host RH, -rsh RH
    The hostname of the redis instance. Defaults to "localhost"

--redis-host REDIS_HOST, -redish REDIS_HOST
    The hostname of the redis instance. Defaults to "localhost"

--redis-port REDIS_PORT, -redisp REDIS_PORT
    The port of the redis instance. Defaults to "6379"

--redis-db REDIS_DB, -redisdb REDIS_DB
    The database to use for the redis instance. Defaults to "0"

--redis-password REDIS_PASS, -redispass REDIS_PASS
    The password to use for the redis instance. Defaults to "None"

--amqp-host AMQP_HOST, -amqph AMQP_HOST
    The hostname of the amqp endpoint. Defaults to "127.0.0.1"

--amqp-vhost AMQP_VHOST, -amqpvh AMQP_VHOST
    The amqp vhost. Defaults to "/"
--amqp-port AMQP_PORT, -amqpp AMQP_PORT
    The port of the amqp endpoint. Defaults to "5672"
--amqp-user AMQP_USER, -amqpu AMQP_USER
    The username to use for the amqp auth. Defaults to "guest"
--amqp-password AMQP_PASS, -amqppass AMQP_PASS
    The password to use for the amqp auth. Defaults to "guest"
--inbound-message-ttl INBOUND_MESSAGE_TTL, -ittl INBOUND_MESSAGE_TTL
    The maximum time allowed to reply to a message. Defaults to 60*10 seconds or 10 minutes
--outbound-message-ttl OUTBOUND_MESSAGE_TTL, -ottl OUTBOUND_MESSAGE_TTL
    The maximum time allowed for events to arrive for messages. Defaults to 60*60*24*2 seconds or 2 days
